    +gaNavbar

    main#ga-main
        div.galileo(style="margin-top:20px; text-align:left;")
            h2 How to answer your own questions by running experiments using Galileo
            //div(style="margin-top:40px;") In an earlier post, we talked about how #[a(href='/galileo/blog/why-exp' target="_blank") scientists test their intuitions by running experiments]. We also saw that with the right tools and support from the community, #[a(href='https://vimeo.com/149413987' target="_blank") anyone can run their own experiments]. Galileo is one such tool, that anyone can use to test their ideas by designing and running experiments! In this post we'll cover how you can contribute to your community using Galileo
            div(style="margin-top:20px;") There are 3 kinds of activities you can perform using Galileo:
                ol
                    li Design your own an experiment
                    li Review someone else's experiment
                    li Participate in someone else's experiment

            div Our easy to use interface will guide you through each of these tasks.
            br
            br
            br

            h4 Designing an experiment

            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div To design an experiment you'll need to start with an intuition. In our example, Alice has the intuition that #[i drinking #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lassi' target="_blank") lassi] (a yogurt based drink) helps in digestion].
                div.col.m7.s12
                    //img(style="width: 100%;" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/1-intuition-fast.gif")
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/1-intuition-medium.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Using Galileo's templates and examples, she breaks down the intuition into a [cause] - [relation] - [effect] format, hence forming a testable hypothesis.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    //img(style="width: 100%;" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/2-breakdown-fast.gif")
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/2-breakdown-medium.mp4")

            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Next, Alice decides how to measure the [cause] in her experiment. She chooses to measure the absence or presence of lassi in the participant's diets. She could also chose other options, like measuring the Amount of lassi (e.g. in cups, or ounces) or Frequency of drinking lassi (e.g. drinking lassi 3 times a day).
                div.col.m7.s12
                    //img(style="width: 100%;" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/2-breakdown-fast.gif")
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/3-measure-cause-medium.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Similarly, she chooses to measure the [effect], i.e. bloatedness on a scale of 1 - 5, where 1 means no bloatedness and 5 means high bloatedness.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/4-measure-effect-medium.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Galileo sends automatic daily notifications to participants, reminding them to report their experiment data. In this step, Alice sets an 8pm notification to ask participants if they drank lassi or not. The reminder text is automatically generated based on the options chosen in previous steps, and can be customized.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/5-reminder.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Similarly, she sets an early morning reminder for participants to measure their bloatedness. Galileo provides expert checklists that remind her to set the reminders at an convenient times.
                    div
                        | If you're confused at any time, you can click the
                        a: i.fa.fa-question-circle(aria-hidden="true")
                        | icons to learn more.

                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/5b-reminder.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Now Alice sets up a control and experimental condition. Galileo provides examples and expert videos to guide you. In this case Alice would compare the control group - where participants won't drink lassi, with the experimental group - where participants will drink lassi.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/6-condition-groups.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Alice now defines clear instructions for participants in control and experimental group. It's important that the instructions are well defined and unambiguous, otherwise participants might end up doing different things.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/7-condition-instructions2.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Next, Alice decides who should or should not participate in her experiment. Any participants that could be harmed while following the instructions should be excluded. Galileo excludes some participants by default, e.g. people under the age of 18 aren't allowed to participate in online experiments on Galileo.
                    div Any participants that could benefit from taking part in the experiment should be included. You can also include specific communities, for example, athletes.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/8-criteria.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Awesome! The final steps shows the summary of the experiment, and some concluding checklists to help the creator improve their own experimental design.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/9-summary.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div You may also make changes to your experiment in the summary page by clicking the edit button.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/10-summary-edit.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Woo-hoo! The experiment is now ready to be reviewed. You can now copy the experiment's share link and invite people to review your experiment.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/11-share-exp.mp4")


            div(style="margin-top:20px;") Galileo will send you notifications as you start getting reviews. Once 2 people have reviewed your experiment, Galileo will guide you through the next steps to help you run the experiment.
            br
            br

            h4 Reviewing an experiment

            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div Bob, another Galileo member, is browsing through all experiments and is interested in reviewing Alice's experiment.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/12a-review-exp.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div The review is broken down into separate sections so that Bob can provide specific feedback about each component of the experiment.
                    br
                    div After reviewing all the sections, Bob clicks on "Finish Review" to submit his feedback.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/12-review-exp.mp4")


            br
            br

            h4 Participating in an experiment


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div After receiving 2 reviews and improving her experiment, Alice is now ready to begin running it. She invites another Galileo member, Joe, to join the experiment using an invite link.
                    br
                    div Before joining, Joe needs to pass the experiment criteria defined by Alice.
                    br
                    div After successfully joining, Joe will be automatically placed in the Control or Experimental group by Galileo. Once the experiment begins he will start receiving text messages relevant to his group.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/13-join-exp.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div An early morning message reminds Joe of what steps to take during the day.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/14-daily-text.mp4")


            div.row(style="margin-top:20px;")
                div.col.m5.s12(style="margin-top:20px;")
                    div A 9am message reminds him to rate his bloatedness, and an 8pm message asks if he drank lassi or not.
                div.col.m7.s12
                    video(controls="controls" width="100%" src="/images/galileo/tutorial/15-text-msg.mp4")


            br
            br
            h4 Conclusion

            div(style="margin-top:20px;") Experimentation is a powerful way to scientifically answer your questions, and researchers run experiment all the time. Now with Galileo, you can be a researcher too!

            div.action-section.container
                br
                div.row
                    div.col.m2
                    div.col.m8.s12
                        a.waves-effect.waves-light.white-text.z-depth-3.light-blue.darken-4.hoverable.modal-trigger#designExp(style="padding:25px; border-radius:6px; text-align:center; width:100%; ") Answer questions about your health!
                    div.col.m2

            div.divider(style="margin:30px 0px;")


